  "prompt": "What is the best way of cooking tapioca?",
  "response": "Here are some good methods for cooking tapioca:\n\n1. For Tapioca Pearls (Bubble Tea):\n- Boil water\n- Add pearls and stir\n- Cook for 15-20 minutes\n- Let sit for another 15-20 minutes\n- Rinse with cold water\n\n2. For Tapioca Pudding:\n- Combine tapioca, milk, sugar, and egg\n- Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly\n- Simmer until thickened (about 15 minutes)\n- Let cool and serve\n\n3. For Small Tapioca:\n- Soak in water for 30 minutes\n- Drain excess water\n- Cook in milk or liquid until transparent and soft\n- Stir frequently to prevent sticking\n\n4. Quick Tips:\n- Always follow package instructions\n- Use plenty of water when cooking\n- Stir regularly to prevent clumping\n- Don't overcook to maintain proper texture\n\nThe best method depends on the type of tapioca and your specific recipe.",
